// FMCSA operating authority, MCS-150 and UCR attach only in interstate commerce; the $5M/$1.5M
// financial-responsibility floors are interstate + capacity tiers; the CDL and the Clearinghouse query are
// the federal floor for any 16+-passenger CMV (interstate OR intrastate, via Texas's adoption of the
// FMCSRs). The DOT medical certificate reaches intrastate drivers ONLY via state adoption (49 CFR part 391
// is interstate-only by federal force; Texas applies it through Transp. Code ch. 644) — it is kept
// capacity-only here as a deliberate coverage-preserving decision while the TX medical rule is
// probable/withheld (see that rule's notes).
